{"word":"Ἑρμῆς","slug":"Ἑρμῆς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Ἑρμῆς, οῦ, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ etym.\">etym.</a> uncertain] <b>Hermes<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> a <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Gk.\">Gk.</a> god, usually associated with role of messenger, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ esp.\">esp.</a> for Zeus <b><a href='B:510 14:12'>Ac 14:12</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> one of Paul’s acquaintances <b><a href='B:520 16:14'>Ro 16:14</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἑρμηνεύω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Ἑρμογένης\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}